The error you're seeing, `error GD0001: Missing partial modifier on declaration of type 'StateOfThePlayer' which is a subclass of 'Godot.GodotObject'`, indicates that Godot's C# support expects to find a partial declaration for the `StateOfThePlayer` class due to it being generated by the Godot source generator as part of the build process. This is likely a requirement of the Godot engine's internal workings for C# scripts that are used as Godot nodes.

To resolve the error, try modifying your `StateOfThePlayer` class declaration in C# to include the `partial` keyword, like this:

```csharp
// StateOfThePlayer.cs
using Godot;
using System;

public partial class StateOfThePlayer : Node
{
    public static StateOfThePlayer Instance { get; private set; }

    public float Health { get; set; }
    public Vector2 Last2DPosition { get; set; }
    public Vector3 Last3DPosition { get; set; }

    public override void _Ready()
    {
        Instance = this;
        // Other initialization code...
    }

    public override void _ExitTree()
    {
        Instance = null;
        // Other cleanup code...
    }
}
```

After making this change, rebuild your project in the Godot editor. You may also want to restart the Godot editor to ensure it recognizes the updated code.

